{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dd4c5e75-08d3-4d13-ade7-c1389dd2e041","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nKey differences: xUnit embeds the skip reason directly in `[Fact]`/`[Theory]` rather than using a separate attribute. The other three use standalone attributes alongside `[TestMethod]`/`[Test]`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"355e22d4-f666-4b97-b188-99c5c5ecc3b4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":327,"requestId":"7C1A:11A664:1237464:14A95AA:69F9436F"},"id":"df4b9bef-a0bb-40bd-b5c4-82c9a2ecec6f","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:10:14.388Z","parentId":"04c0cd71-64b8-415f-bcea-efafbf691af0"}
